THE TIANA. UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. THE Motor Boat “TIANA,” etc., Stillman Delehanty Ferris Company, Appellee. No. 267. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 1, 1937.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

Lamar Hardy, U. S. Atty., and Mary R. Towle, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of New York City, for the United States. Burlingham, Veeder, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Norman M. Barron, of Ney York City, of counsel), for appellee. PER CURIAM.

Decree (- F.Supp. -) affirmed on opinion below.
